---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Peptide Price Lab - Per-mg Peptide Price Comparison Tool"
description: "Compare research peptide prices per milligram across top vendors. Find the best value, optimize bundles, and track sources — all in one free tool."
ogTitle: "Peptide Price Lab — Per-mg Peptide Price Comparison"
ogDescription: "The free research tool for comparing peptide prices per mg across vendors. Stop overpaying. Start comparing."
ogImage: "https://peptidepricelab.com/assets/og-image.png"
schema:
  "@context": "https://schema.org"
  "@type": "SoftwareApplication"
  name: "Peptide Price Lab"
  url: "https://app.peptidepricelab.com"
  applicationCategory: "UtilitiesApplication"
  operatingSystem: "Web"
  description: "Per-mg peptide price comparison and bundle optimizer for research use."
  offers: { "@type": "Offer", price: "0", priceCurrency: "USD" }
---

{# ── Hero ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="hp-hero">
  <div class="hp-hero-main">
    <div class="eyebrow">The Cover Story · Issue Fourteen</div>
    <h1 class="hp-hero-title">Stop guessing<br>what a milligram<br><span class="italic">actually costs.</span></h1>
    <p class="hp-hero-lede">A free, vendor-neutral calculator for the only number that matters when you're sourcing research peptides — the price per milligram.</p>
    <div class="hp-hero-cta">
      <a href="{{ site.appUrl }}" class="btn-cta">Compare prices now →</a>
      <a href="/start-here/" class="hp-hero-link">Or — read what peptides actually are</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <aside class="hp-receipt" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="hp-receipt-head">BPC-157 · Per-mg Receipt</div>
    <div class="hp-receipt-row"><span>Vendor A · 5 mg · $28</span><span>$5.60</span></div>
    <div class="hp-receipt-row"><span>Vendor B · 10 mg · $45</span><span>$4.50</span></div>
    <div class="hp-receipt-row"><span>Vendor C · 5 mg · $34</span><span>$6.80</span></div>
    <div class="hp-receipt-row"><span>Vendor D · 10 mg · $52</span><span>$5.20</span></div>
    <div class="hp-receipt-rule"></div>
    <div class="hp-receipt-row hp-receipt-best"><span>Best value</span><span>$4.50/mg</span></div>
    <div class="hp-receipt-note">You'd pay 51% more buying the "cheap" vial.</div>
  </aside>
</section>

{# ── Trust bar ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="hp-trust">
  <div class="hp-trust-item"><span class="hp-trust-n">412</span><span class="hp-trust-l">Products tracked</span></div>
  <div class="hp-trust-item"><span class="hp-trust-n">18</span><span class="hp-trust-l">Vendors indexed</span></div>
  <div class="hp-trust-item"><span class="hp-trust-n">$0</span><span class="hp-trust-l">To use, ever</span></div>
  <div class="hp-trust-item"><span class="hp-trust-n">Weekly</span><span class="hp-trust-l">Per-mg refresh</span></div>
</section>

{# ── The Index ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="hp-section">
  <div class="hp-section-head">
    <div class="hp-mark"><span class="hp-mark-num">§ 01</span> The Index</div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="hp-section-title">What we're <span class="italic">tracking</span> this week.</h2>
      <p class="hp-section-dek">The peptides our readers are pricing most — with the current per-mg low and high across the eighteen vendors we index. Click any row for the research notes.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hp-index">
    <div class="hp-index-head">
      <span>№</span><span>Compound</span><span>Notes</span><span>Per-mg range</span>
    </div>
    {% set shown = 0 %}
    {% for note in collections.researchNotes %}
      {% if note.data.price and shown < 8 %}
        {% set shown = shown + 1 %}
        <a href="{{ note.url }}" class="hp-index-row">
          <span class="hp-index-num">{{ '%02d' | format(shown) if false else shown }}</span>
          <span class="hp-index-name">{{ note.data.peptideName or note.data.h1 or note.data.title }}</span>
          <span class="hp-index-cat">{{ note.data.category or (note.data.tags[0] if note.data.tags) }}</span>
          <span class="hp-index-price"><b>{{ note.data.price.low }}</b> — {{ note.data.price.high }} <i>/mg</i></span>
        </a>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <a href="/peptides/" class="hp-more">The full index, every compound →</a>
</section>

{# ── Editor's note ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="hp-section hp-section--paper">
  <div class="hp-section-head">
    <div class="hp-mark"><span class="hp-mark-num">§ 02</span> Editor's Note</div>
    <div class="hp-editorial">
      <p class="hp-editorial-lead"><span class="hp-dropcap">A</span> five-milligram vial for twenty-eight dollars <em>sounds</em> cheaper than a ten-milligram vial for forty-five. Per milligram, that "cheap" vial costs $5.60 against $4.50 for the larger one.</p>
      <p>Multiply across a year of research and the difference isn't small — it's often the cost of a whole extra protocol. Vendors know this, which is precisely why pricing is rarely presented per milligram.</p>
      <p>We built the Lab because nobody we trusted was doing the math out loud. We do use affiliate codes — but only when they're actually the better deal. If a vendor's running a sale that beats our code, we say so. That's what keeps the Lab free and ad-free.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── Pledge ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
{% set pledgeVariant = "wide" %}
{% include "partials/pledge.njk" %}

{# ── Sources ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="hp-section">
  <div class="hp-section-head">
    <div class="hp-mark"><span class="hp-mark-num">§ 03</span> The Sources</div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="hp-section-title">The vendors, <span class="italic">indexed</span> &amp; annotated.</h2>
      <p class="hp-section-dek">Eighteen vendors with current shipping &amp; COA notes — none of them paid to be here.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="hp-sources">
    {% for v in ["Peptide Sciences","Core Peptides","Swiss Chems","Biotech Peptides","Loti Labs","Pinnacle Peptides"] %}
      <a href="/sources/" class="hp-source-row"><span class="hp-source-name">{{ v }}</span><span class="hp-source-go">View →</span></a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <a href="/sources/" class="hp-more">All 18 vendors →</a>
</section>

{# ── Dispatch ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="hp-dispatch">
  <div class="hp-dispatch-main">
    <div class="eyebrow">The Saturday Dispatch</div>
    <h2 class="hp-dispatch-title">Price drops, plain-language briefs, <span class="italic">one Saturday morning.</span></h2>
    <p class="hp-dispatch-dek">A short, honest letter on what's moved in the per-mg market — and what new research is actually worth reading.</p>
    {% if collections.dispatch %}
      <div class="hp-dispatch-issues">
        {% for issue in collections.dispatch %}
          {% if loop.index <= 2 %}
            <a href="{{ issue.url }}" class="hp-dispatch-issue">
              <span class="hp-dispatch-num">{{ issue.data.issueNumber }}<br>{{ issue.data.date | readableDate }}</span>
              <span class="hp-dispatch-headline">{{ issue.data.h1 or issue.data.title }}</span>
            </a>
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
  <form class="subscribe-form" action="{{ site.newsletterAction or '#' }}" method="post">
    <span class="form-label">Subscribe — it's free</span>
    <p class="form-prompt">One short letter, Saturday at 7&nbsp;a.m. Eastern.</p>
    <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required>
    <button type="submit">Send me the Dispatch</button>
    <div class="form-trust"><div>≈ 4,800 readers · No selling lists, ever</div></div>
  </form>
</section>
